---
import QuizLayout from '../../../../layouts/QuizLayout.astro';
---

<QuizLayout
  title="Your Result: The Preventer — Apron Belly Guide"
  description="You're in the prevention window — the most effective time to act on apron belly. Here's your personalized starting protocol."
>

<style is:global>
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }

.res-wrap {
  max-width: 680px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 1.25rem 5rem;
}

.res-header {
  padding: 2rem 1.25rem 0;
  max-width: 680px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
}
.res-logo {
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  color: #2D2A26;
  text-decoration: none;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}
.res-logo:hover { color: #7A9E7E; }

.res-badge {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  background: #EFF6EF;
  border: 1.5px solid #C3D9C4;
  border-radius: 100px;
  padding: 0.35rem 0.9rem;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: #4F7A52;
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
}
.res-badge::before { content: '●'; font-size: 0.5rem; color: #7A9E7E; }

h1.res-headline {
  font-size: clamp(1.55rem, 4.5vw, 2.2rem);
  font-weight: 800;
  color: #2D2A26;
  line-height: 1.2;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.res-diag {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: #6B6560;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #EBE7E0;
}

.res-section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.res-section h2 {
  font-size: 0.68rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  color: #A09890;
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
.res-section p {
  font-size: 0.97rem;
  color: #4A4540;
  line-height: 1.75;
}

.res-good { background: #F4FAF4; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-left: 3px solid #7A9E7E; }
.res-honest { background: #FAF8F5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-left: 3px solid #D4CFC9; }

.res-protocol {
  margin: 2.5rem 0;
  padding-top: 2.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid #EBE7E0;
}
.res-protocol h2 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #2D2A26;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}
.res-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; }
.res-step {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
  align-items: flex-start;
}
.res-step-num {
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: #7A9E7E;
  color: white;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 0.1rem;
}
.res-step-body strong {
  display: block;
  font-size: 0.97rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #2D2A26;
  margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
}
.res-step-body p {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #6B6560;
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin: 0;
}

.res-ctas {
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  padding-top: 2.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid #EBE7E0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.875rem;
}
.res-cta-primary {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: #7A9E7E;
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  padding: 0.9rem 2rem;
  border-radius: 12px;
  transition: opacity 0.15s, transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 14px rgba(122,158,126,0.32);
  text-align: center;
}
.res-cta-primary:hover {
  opacity: 0.93;
  transform: translateY(-1px);
  box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(122,158,126,0.38);
}
.res-cta-secondary {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: white;
  color: #4A4540;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 0.93rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1.5px solid #E8E4DE;
  transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
  text-align: center;
}
.res-cta-secondary:hover { border-color: #7A9E7E; background: #F6FAF6; }

.res-retake {
  margin-top: 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: #C4BDB6;
}
.res-retake a { color: #A09890; text-decoration: none; }
.res-retake a:hover { color: #7A9E7E; }

@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .res-header { padding: 2rem 2rem 0; }
  .res-wrap { padding: 0 2rem 5rem; }
}
</style>

<header class="res-header">
  <a href="/" class="res-logo">Apron Belly Guide</a>
</header>

<main class="res-wrap">
  <p class="res-badge">Your Profile: The Preventer</p>
  <h1 class="res-headline">You're in the Prevention Window — the Most Effective Time to Act</h1>
  <p class="res-diag">Most people dealing with apron belly wish they had started earlier. You're starting earlier. That changes what's possible.</p>

  <div class="res-section">
    <h2>What your answers show</h2>
    <p>You're currently losing weight and want to protect your skin before significant laxity develops. This is the single best position to be in — interventions that support skin elasticity <em>during</em> weight loss are meaningfully more effective than trying to reverse loose skin after the fact.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="res-section res-good">
    <h2>The good news</h2>
    <p>Prevention is real. The collagen remodeling process is active right now, while your skin is adapting to change. Supporting it during this window — rather than waiting until after weight loss ends — produces better outcomes by every measure.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="res-section res-honest" style="margin-top:1rem;">
    <h2>The honest part</h2>
    <p>Prevention reduces the problem. It doesn't guarantee zero loose skin. Age, genetics, how much you ultimately lose, and how long the skin was stretched are factors you can influence but can't fully override. The goal is to maximize what's within your control.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="res-protocol">
    <h2>Your starting protocol — in priority order</h2>
    <div class="res-steps">
      <div class="res-step">
        <div class="res-step-num">1</div>
        <div class="res-step-body">
          <strong>Start collagen now, not after</strong>
          <p>10g/day of hydrolyzed collagen peptides. The timing matters: starting during weight loss supports skin structure while it's actively remodeling. Most people wait until they've finished losing weight. Don't.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="res-step">
        <div class="res-step-num">2</div>
        <div class="res-step-body">
          <strong>Do not skip strength training</strong>
          <p>Muscle preservation during fat loss is the second-biggest determinant of skin outcome. Resistance training 2–3x per week protects muscle mass and builds structure beneath the skin as fat is lost.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="res-step">
        <div class="res-step-num">3</div>
        <div class="res-step-body">
          <strong>Weekly microneedling on at-risk areas</strong>
          <p>A 0.5mm derma roller used weekly on the abdomen stimulates collagen production in the skin as it's being asked to retract. Low cost, consistent signal to the dermis.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="res-ctas">
    <a href="/weight-loss/how-to-prevent-loose-skin/" class="res-cta-primary">Read the Full Prevention Guide →</a>
    <a href="/non-surgical-solutions/" class="res-cta-secondary">Browse All Non-Surgical Options</a>
  </div>

  <p class="res-retake">Not quite right? <a href="/quiz/">Retake the assessment</a></p>
</main>

</QuizLayout>
